  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A vial of fully distilled Laublub oil, almost clear with a faint luminous shimmer. The purest and most potent grade.</p><h2>Drink</h2><p>Target a creature and choose how many charges to feed it (Consumption Scaling). Each charge consumed restores 1 hour to the target's fluid gauge, up to the 48-hour cap.</p><h2>Douse</h2><p>Pour charges onto the ground to coat the area with oil (radius scales with charges spent: 1 charge = 2.5 ft radius, 2 = 3.75 ft, 3 = 5 ft). Any creature entering or starting its turn there must succeed on a DC 10 + the douser's Dexterity modifier Dexterity saving throw or fall prone (and take 1d12 fire damage if the oil has been ignited; standing up requires the same save). The oil evaporates after 2 minutes. Igniting is GM adjudicated and grants a one-time +8 bonus to the triggering fire damage.</p><h2>Throw</h2><p>Ranged attack roll against a creature or object. On a hit, the target is coated in oil for 60 rounds. At the start of its turn, the target may spend its action and succeed on a DC 10 Dexterity saving throw to reduce the remaining duration by 5 rounds. Igniting (GM adjudicated) grants a one-time +8 bonus to the triggering fire damage; the oil then continues burning for 2 rounds until the end of the target's next turn, dealing an additional 2d8 fire damage at the start of that turn (use the Continued Burn Damage activity).</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
